<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'><font size=3D3
face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>Dear Program
Committee Member,<br>
<br>
We have the pleasure to send you the first call for tutorials and =
workshops.
Although the call will be distributed to a relatively large mailing =
list, you
are welcome not only to further publicize it among your contacts, but =
also
encourage that we get a good response. <br>
<br>
</span></font>Best regards,<br>
<br>
The Conference chairs:<br>
<br>
Pavel Brazdil, Jo=E3o Gama, Lu=EDs Torgo, Rui Camacho, Al=EDpio =
Jorge<br>
<br>
<b><span style=3D'font-weight:bold'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'><b><font size=3D3
face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;font-weight:
bold'>***************************************<br>
**=A0=A0 ECML/PKDD-2005<br>
**=A0=A0 </span><span lang=3DIT>Call for Tutorials and Workshops<br>
***************************************</span></font></b><b><span =
lang=3DEN-US
style=3D'font-weight:bold'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoBodyText style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'><font size=3D3
face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>The
ECML/PKDD-2005 Organizing Committee invites proposals for tutorials and
workshops that will be co-located with the main ECML/PKDD-2005 =
conference, <st1:place
w:st=3D"on"><st1:City w:st=3D"on">Porto</st1:City>, <st1:country-region =
w:st=3D"on">Portugal</st1:country-region></st1:place>.
We invite proposals for half-day tutorials and full day workshops. =
Proposals
for a workshop/tutorial combination are also welcome (see below). The =
scope of
the proposal should be consistent with the conference themes as =
described in
the ECML/PKDD-2005 Call for Papers (see the conference site, =
http://ecmlpkdd05.liacc.up.pt,
for details).<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoBodyText style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'><b><font size=3D3
face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;font-weight:
bold'>* Workshops</span></font></b><span lang=3DEN-US>: These provide an
opportunity to discuss current topics in machine learning and/or data =
mining in
a small and interactive atmosphere. Thus, any topic that is of current =
interest
to a sufficient number of participants from the two communities could be =
the
focus of a workshop. Workshops can concentrate in-depth on research =
topics, but
can also be devoted to application issues, or to questions concerning =
the
economic and social aspects of machine learning and data mining.
Multidisciplinary workshops that bring together researchers and =
practitioners
from different communities such as advanced computing and GRID, =
database,
ontology, life science, cognitive science, economics and finance, =
mathematics
and operations research, are welcome.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoBodyText style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'><b><font size=3D3
face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;font-weight:
bold'>* Tutorials</span></font></b><span lang=3DEN-US>: These are =
intended to
provide independent instruction on topics from the field of machine =
learning or
data mining. Introductions to other research domains that could =
fertilize the machine
learning/data mining field with new challenges or solutions are also =
welcome
provided that there is a clear relation to machine learning/data mining. =
Each
tutorial should:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<ul style=3D'margin-top:0cm' type=3Ddisc>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>attract a
     large enough audience; <o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>be
     presented by highly qualified persons with a demonstrable =
background and
     teaching experience in the tutorial area; =
<o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>be
     well-focused, so that its core content can be covered in a 3.5 hour
     tutorial slot (incl. a 30 minute break); =
<o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>be
     accompanied by comprehensive notes written in clear, standard =
English; <o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>cope with
     the wide diversity in the ECML/PKDD audience (preferable), or else =
be
     accompanied by a complete list of tutorial prerequisites; =
<o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>cover the
     overall picture, without a bias towards the presenters' own work; =
<o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>be free
     of commercial or sales-oriented material. =
<o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
</ul>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify'><font size=3D3
face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'><br>
As workshops and tutorials are in a sense complementary, we also welcome
proposals for combined tutorial-workshop events. The general idea is =
that the
tutorial gives an introduction to the field of the workshop, making the
workshop accessible to a broader audience. <o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoBodyText style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'><b><font size=3D3
face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;font-weight:
bold'><br>
** Workshop Participation and Proceedings =
**<o:p></o:p></span></font></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoBodyText style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'><font size=3D3
face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>All workshop
participants are required to register for the main conference. During
registration the participants will specify which workshop they are going =
to
attend. If the workshop organizers intend to allow access to the =
workshop by
invitation only, or would like to see the number of participants =
limited, then
they should clearly indicate so. To make it easier for workshop =
organizers to
attract invited speakers, a limited number of invited speakers (e.g. one =
per
workshop) can be allowed without registration for the main conference, =
provided
they do not attend the main conference. <o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoBodyText style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'><font size=3D3
face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>Workshop
proceedings have to be prepared camera-ready by the workshop organizers =
(in a
form of a single PDF file). They will be printed by the ECML/PKDD =
organizers. A
common paper style will be adopted for the proceedings (Springer =
format).<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoBodyText style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'><font size=3D3
face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>In addition,
the ECML/PKDD organizers intend to prepare a CD containing all the =
workshop
proceedings. Hence, electronic submissions to the workshops are =
essential so
that this could be carried out.=A0 <o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<h1 style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'><b><font size=3D3 face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
lang=3DEN-US style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'><br>
** Tutorial participation and publication of =
materials**<o:p></o:p></span></font></b></h1>

<p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><font size=3D3
face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>Registered
conference participants can freely attend all tutorials. =
<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><font size=3D3
face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>Tutorial
presenters are expected to prepare hand-outs for the audience (PDF =
file), which
will be printed by the ECML/PKDD organizers. The organizers also plan to =
make
the tutorial materials available on the CD containing the workshop =
materials. Consequently,
tutorial presenters are expected to make their materials available =
several
weeks before the start of the conference (see the list with Important =
dates). <o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify'><font size=3D3
face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>Discounts on
registration will be considered for the tutorial =
presenters.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<h1 style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'><b><font size=3D3 face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
lang=3DEN-US style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'><br>
** Important dates =A0**<o:p></o:p></span></font></b></h1>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 face=3D"Times New Roman"><span =
lang=3DIT
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>- Workshop proposal deadline: 28 March =
&#8216;05<br>
- Tutorial proposal deadline: 18 April <br>
- Workshop acceptance notification: 18 April <br>
- Tutorial acceptance notification 18 May<br>
- Workshop Call for Papers (to be ready on the web): 9 May<br>
- Tutorial summary (to be ready on the web):=A0 9 June<br>
- Workshop paper submission deadline: 25 July <br>
- Workshop paper acceptance notification: 15 August<br>
- Workshop paper camera-ready deadline: 5 Sept.<br>
- Workshop proceedings (camera-ready): 12 Sept.<br>
- Tutorial notes (camera-ready): 12 Sept.<br>
- Start of the conference: 3 Oct. &#8216;05<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><span style=3D'font-weight:bold'>** How to Propose a Workshop=A0 =
**<o:p></o:p></span></b></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoBodyText style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'><font size=3D3
face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>Workshop proposals
should contain the necessary information for the workshop chairs and =
reviewers
to judge the importance, quality and community interest in the proposed =
topic.
Each workshop should have one or more designated organizers and a =
workshop
program or organizing committee. When proposing a workshop, please =
provide (at
least) the following information:<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<ul style=3D'margin-top:0cm' type=3Ddisc>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>A brief
     technical description of the specific technical issues that the =
workshop
     will address.<o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>The
     reasons why the workshop is of interest this time. =
<o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>The names,
     postal and email addresses, phone and fax numbers of the Workshop =
Chairs.
     At least one of the Workshop Chairs should be a knowledgeable =
person in
     the area of machine learning or data =
mining.<o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>The
     names, affiliations and email addresses of the Workshop Program =
Committee.<o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>A list of
     previously-organized related workshops by any of the Workshop =
Chairs,
     although previous experience with similar workshops is not =
required. <o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>If
     possible, a list of potential attendees if the proposal of the =
workshop were
     accepted.=A0 Estimate of the number of potential participants and =
their main
     research areas (machine learning, data mining, database, =
statistics,
     logics, life science, finance, &#8230;). =
<o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>How the
     workshop will be publicized. <o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>A summary
     of the intended workshop Call for Participation, showing how the
     organizers will encourage a workshop, rather than a =
mini-conference,
     atmosphere (e.g., invited talks, presentations, panel discussions, =
or
     other ideas for ensuring an interactive =
atmosphere).<o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>Plans to
     document the workshop results (beyond ECML/PKDDS publication). =
<o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>Ideal
     duration of the workshop (three/ four =
sessions).<o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>A list of
     audio-visual or technical requirements and any special room =
requirements.<o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>In the
     case of a combined tutorial-workshop proposal: title of the =
tutorial and
     name of proposers. <o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1'><font size=3D3
     face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>Proposers
     are encouraged to send their draft proposal to the potential =
participants
     for comments before submission. <o:p></o:p></span></font></li>
</ul>

<p class=3DMsoBodyText><font size=3D3 face=3D"Times New Roman"><span =
lang=3DEN-US
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'><br>
Please submit your workshop proposals by e-mail to ECML/PKDD workshop =
chair
(see contact information below). He/she will review the proposals in =
close
collaboration with the tutorial chair, conference chairs and the program
committee.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<h1 style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'><b><font size=3D3 face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
lang=3DEN-US style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'><br>
** How to Propose a Tutorial =A0**<o:p></o:p></span></font></b></h1>

<p class=3DMsoNormal =
style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><font size=3D3
face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>Tutorial
proposals should contain all information that the proposer considers to =
be
relevant for judging the relevance of the tutorial. In particular, it =
should
contain (1) title of the tutorial and a short overview of the area that =
will be
covered, (2) an outline of the tutorial in the form of a structured list =
of
topics, (3) a description of the target audience and expected prior =
knowledge, and
(4) information about the scientific qualifications of the presenter(s)
including their experience on teaching the material of the tutorial, if
possible (5) accompanied by some sample material (e.g., slides or =
hand-outs
from a previous tutorial or a course the presenters have taught). =
<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoBodyText><font size=3D3 face=3D"Times New Roman"><span =
lang=3DEN-US
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>All materials should be submitted by e-mail =
to the
ECML/PKDD tutorial chair (see contact information below). He/she will =
review
the proposal in close collaboration with the workshop chair, conference =
chairs
and the program committee.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<h3 style=3D'margin-bottom:6.0pt'><b><font size=3D3 face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
lang=3DEN-US style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'><br>
**=A0 How to Propose a Tutorial/Workshop Combination=A0 =
**<o:p></o:p></span></font></b></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify'><font size=3D3
face=3D"Times New Roman"><span lang=3DEN-US =
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt'>Proposals for
joint tutorial-workshop events can be made by sending the joint proposal =
to both
the workshop and the tutorial chair, clearly indicating on each proposal =
that
this is a joint event, and also stating reasons why such a joint event =
is
preferable to just a workshop or tutorial. It is possible for joint =
proposals
that only the workshop or tutorial part will be accepted. =
<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

